<paragraph blockId="9.[820,1468,1866,1956]" lastBlockId="10.[119,767,133,188]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Description of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Porter, Hoofer, Cline, Hoffman, &amp; Baker" authorityYear="2007" box="[1095,1219,1901,1921]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leuconycteris">
<emphasis box="[1095,1219,1901,1921]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leuconycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Porter, C. A. &amp; Hoofer, S. R. &amp; Cline, C. A. &amp; Hoffmann, F. G. &amp; Baker, R. J." box="[1253,1433,1901,1921]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Mammalogy" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1205 - 1215" part="88" refId="ref18424" refString="Porter, C. A., Hoofer, S. R., Cline, C. A., Hoffmann, F. G., &amp; Baker, R. J. (2007). Molecular phylogenetics of the phyllostomid bat genus Micronycteris with descriptions of two new subgenera. Journal of Mammalogy, 88, 1205 - 1215. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 06 - MAMM-A- 292 R. 1" title="Molecular phylogenetics of the phyllostomid bat genus Micronycteris with descriptions of two new subgenera" type="journal article" year="2007">Porter et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
did not include 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1086,1936,1956]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schmidtorum">
<emphasis box="[936,1086,1936,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">M. schmidtorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Porter, Hoofer, Cline, Hoffman, &amp; Baker" authorityYear="2007" box="[1098,1222,1936,1956]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leuconycteris">
<emphasis box="[1098,1222,1936,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leuconycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1866" box="[119,242,133,153]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[119,242,133,153]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Micronycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which includes all the small (FA &lt;
<quantity box="[585,669,133,153]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="39.5">39.5 mm</quantity>
) dark-bellied members of the genus.
</paragraph>
